When i first started playing css i played aim_noob as my first map online and since i enjoyed playing it with other players i often tried to search for it, but there arent any servers playing that map so i decided to make a remake of it. And decided to call it aim_buddha. SInce its based on aim_noob and i have no idea who the author of it was/is i can only writte unknown. Thanks to whoever you are for my first experience with css. 
-------------------------------------------------------------
Aim_buddha is a fast action map two flanks for each side and also a stair on both sides to go up on the walls. It has a open arena with cover walls on both sides and is kept in the popular de_dust styled geometry. 
Can be used for Normal Gameplay / Team-Deathmatch(maybe not too good) / GunGame 
Would be very happy to see my first map getting played on just one server.
------------------------------
INSTALL
------------------------------
Place the bsp and nav file in cstrike/maps
---------------------------------------------------
Diffrences from the original and to the remake:
Map has info_nodes for bots
Map has cubemaps
Map has light
Map has now also has Fog
Map is open
Map has a little more detail and a little more walkable areas
----------------------------------------------------------------------
The Map has 9 spawns for both teams so the map doesnt get crowded too much
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Since this is my first release of css maps dont be too hard :)
----------------------------------------------------------------------

Changes:
- A new builded and cutted bridge(looks better and needs less)

Back to the roots man! :D 13 yerars ago valve showed us what the source engine can deliver. A lot physics, a lot small brushes, reflections....... 

aim_bridgecut shows what the source engine is, it shows the strengts of this engine. You can see this also in Titanfall 2, no other engine can deliver so much different things at the same time. This is why "I" use this engine. This is why we all use this engine, it delivers just the best performence. So, you can do a lot crazy things, combined with a great performance.....and I will do this. ;D

Sooo, here is now the update for my map aim_bridgecut
It runs how it runs. On a good cpu (i7) with min 89 frames(130 average), ok for this map, but it's a lot for this game. This needs cpu power like a new AAA game, but runs on a lowbudged gpu. An amd quad apu (80€) can handle this with 60 frames (tested in 1360x768) And a used phenom 2 quadcore cpu for around 30€ will do this even better. In my eyes is this really cheap, midclass cpus are really not expensive, compered with gpus. My GTX 980Ti  needs 20% gpu and 1830mb vram @120 frames in 2560x1440. Yes for source maybe much, but compared with other games is this again really good. PS: You have 50-80% more frames with lowering the water settings ;)

Update: 3 days later
The most people will think that I say shit, or that the map have some big issues. Fact is the compile is now running the 6. day, I think it will end today..... "I" think it's normal ;/, this amount of information is just a bit too crazy for source. Combined with the water and my vis optimization, you have s*** like this.

And I make this really just for a little fps boost, the final compile needs without hint/skip textures just 42 minutes (just^^).

 If you have no big visblockers like in this map, you must think really small, to make it faster. Bridgecut_ov have needed 57 hours for the compile, this is crazy and makes no fun, but 38% more frames are really a difference and in my eyes is this no wasted time.

I think the new one will make not a big difference, I've add some new hint/skip textures, thats why the compile time is now really horrible, but I think this will just compensate the things I've added here;/. I don't know, I have to wait xD...........

Thats why I can't actually show some new pics.

The vmf. filesize is 17mb, must I say more xD... (official maps: 2-9mb)

Update:  A dream is come true. This is what I wanted, as I started this 6 years ago. It's now exactly my vision and I'm so happy to release this baby now. This is all so impossible for an hobby artist like me and it was a long and hard way......

Release: It will come tommorrow ;)

The best way to test the map is to make a trailer for it, so here is now the trailer for bridgecut_ovl, have fun with it and leave a like, or better a comment ;D

Bridgecut was an experiment for me. How far can i push the source engine? How much details can I add? How much realtime reflectiones? how much physics? and and and......
At the end, I reached 3 limits that makes the map unplayable.

1. I reached the brush limit on this map, so the bsp can not created, yes on an aim_map^^ Over 100 brushes to much and the background was unfinished. That was really shit.

2. I have have testet hdr lighting and it was to much for the vrad, maybe makable without the light switches.

3. At the end i have to much entities in the map and i must reduce, or optimize things, it was crazy, if i placed a new entitie, i must delete 1 or 2 other to make room for it.

Thats why my project called overloaded

The map is really great, it looks awesome and things like the automats or the codelock make it more interaktive.

The problem is the performence, 70fps min are not really great for an i7.

I spent years of work on this map, with the intention to do things, that nobody do. Things that I cant do. My first textures are the textures in this map. It was so hard at the beginning. But now i can create everything what need.  It's just learning by doing. Today i can do so much more things and i work faster and faster. So the work was not just for the map, it was for my comlete project, for ovl! Now i have over 220 self created textures in a nearly perfect quality. :)

The map makes on some servers problems. I dont know why, but I have a

door soundloop bug on my server. But just one door, the other doors are working. The soundloop are just not stopping, really frustrating and not playable!Offline, I hear no problems.

If anybody knows about a config that fix this, please pm me. Thanks :)

This is a very symmetrical map. Each team has two spawn points. The big block in the center of each spawn is destructible hence the name. Also the dark barriers in the center are destructible. Personally I think this map would be best for a gun game, but it'll still work on a gun game server either way. I made it primarily to test out skies, skybox, HDR, and func_rotating.

Map by me (urt555)
Inspired by Robixn's fake DMM with physboxes.
File go here:
C:\Program Files\Steam\steamapps\{YOUR STEAM NAME}\counter-strike source\cstrike\maps

I've worked non-stop all day yesterday and today to fix up this map and make it as fun as possible. This map is called breakable hellhole for a reason. Almost 80% of the brushes are either physboxes (meaning they can move) or breakable. This map requires the skill to snipe with the scout, awp, or autosnipers (if you can get to them). Or if you decide to somehow get close enough to the enemy, whip out a nade or deagle.
Change Log Added -Added More obstacles -Added Physboxes -Added Deagles and grenades in the middle -Added ammo to the Scouts and Awps Fixes / Changes -Optimized -Fixed Cubemaps -Improved Lighting -Fixed texture tiling -Changed textures of almost everything -Fixed the breakable objects acting as glass -Fixed Mis-Aligned textures -Added displacements to riverbed -Expanded kill triggers -Fixed Breakable brushes health for better gameplay. -Fixed basically everything
This map is a lot of fun with online players (but not bots!!) Enjoy :)
